gkwreg 1.1.0
  • Reference

    Predict Method for Generalized Kumaraswamy Regression Models

    predict.gkwreg.Rd

    Obtains predictions and related quantities from a fitted Generalized Kumaraswamy regression model.

    # S3 method for class 'gkwreg'
predict(
  object,
  newdata = NULL,
  type = c("response", "link", "parameter", "alpha", "beta", "gamma", "delta", "lambda",
    "variance", "density", "pdf", "probability", "cdf", "quantile"),
  na.action = stats::na.pass,
  at = 0.5,
  elementwise = NULL,
  family = NULL,
  ...
)

    Arguments

    object

    A fitted model object of class "gkwreg".

    newdata

    Optionally, a data frame with new data. If omitted, the original data is used.

    type

    Character indicating type of prediction required:

    • "response" or "mean": predicted mean of the response (default)

    • "link": linear predictors for all parameters

    • "parameter": all distribution parameters (alpha, beta, gamma, delta, lambda)

    • "alpha", "beta", "gamma", "delta", "lambda": individual parameters

    • "variance": variance of the response

    • "density" or "pdf": density function at values specified by 'at'

    • "probability" or "cdf": cumulative distribution function at 'at'

    • "quantile": quantiles of the distribution at probabilities 'at'

    na.action

    Function determining what to do with missing values in newdata.

    at

    Numeric vector at which to evaluate the prediction function for types "density", "probability", or "quantile".

    elementwise

    Logical. Should each element of the distribution only be evaluated at the corresponding element of 'at' (TRUE) or at all elements in 'at' (FALSE).

    family

    Character string specifying the distribution family to use. If NULL (default), uses the family from the fitted model. Available options: "gkw", "bkw", "kkw", "ekw", "mc", "kw", "beta".

    ...

    Further arguments passed to methods.

    Value

    A vector, matrix, or data frame of predictions, depending on the type.

    Examples

    if (FALSE) { # \dontrun{
# Fit a GKw model
model <- gkwreg(y ~ x1 | x2 | 1 | 1 | 1, data = mydata, family = "gkw")

# Predictions on new data
newdata <- data.frame(x1 = seq(0, 1, by = 0.1), x2 = rep(0, 11))

# Predict mean response
predict(model, newdata, type = "response")

# Predict parameters
predict(model, newdata, type = "parameter")

# Predict densities at specific points
predict(model, newdata, type = "density", at = c(0.2, 0.5, 0.8))

# Predict using a different family than what was fitted
predict(model, newdata, type = "response", family = "beta")
} # }
